Name: Leinster
Description: Leinster is the easternmost province, including Dublin, Ireland's capital and largest city. It is the political and cultural heart of the country.

Name: Munster
Description: Munster is a southwestern province known for its scenic landscapes, historic cities like Cork, and its coastal charm.

Name: Connacht
Description: Connacht is located on the western coast of Ireland, known for its rugged landscapes, historic sites, and the vibrant city of Galway.

Name: Ulster
Description: Ulster is the northernmost province, with a blend of Irish and Northern Irish culture. It contains the city of Belfast in Northern Ireland and Derry in the Republic of Ireland.
